      "label": "Transcript",
      "value": "With papers of 1750 [written in corner of paper in pencil at later date]\n\nTo the President and Worthy Members of the St. Andrews Club in Charles Town.\n\nThe Humble Petition of the poor unfortunate John Mandensell\n\nSheweth\n\nThat your poor Petr. [petitioner] is not only Old and Infirm, but is also grievously Afflicted with Rhumatic [rheumatic] pains in all his Joints, the Cramp and Convulsion of the Nerves all which renders him often unable to feed or help himself, besides which he has a Rupture in his Groin, which Creats [creates] him more trouble and pain than all his other disorders\n\nTherefore your Petr. most humbly prays all your Worthy and Benevolent Members to take his unfortunate and Miserable Case into Consideration and Extend your Charity and Bounty to him in such manner as to you in your goodness Shall seem meet\n\nAnd yr [your] Petr in duty bound will ever pray so\n\nJohn Mandensell\n\n[P.S.] 20 pounds\nCharity to MacClellens Child Contd"
    },
